body.name: Thermalright AXP90 X36 Low Profile ITX CPU Cooler, 36mm Height, TL-9015 Slim PWM CPU Fan, Computer ITX Heatsink Cooler, for AMD:AM4 AM5/Intel LGA1150/1151/1200/1700

features: 【Brand Overview】Thermalright is a Taiwan brand with more than 20 years of development. It has a certain popularity in the domestic and foreign markets and has a pivotal influence in the player market. We have been focusing on the research and development of computer accessories. R & D product lines include: CPU cooler radiator, case fan, thermal silicone pad, thermal conductive paste, support mounting bracket and other commodities.

【AGHP technique】4×6mm heat pipes apply AGHP technique, Solve the Inverse gravity effect caused by vertical / horizontal orientation,the cooling effect of the cpu cooler is also doubled by the process of secondary welding of heat pipes and fins.

【36mm Height】The AXP90 X36 low profile cooler, combined with a 92mm PWM fan for automatic temperature control and ultra-quiet operation, and a total cooler height of just 36mm, makes it ideal for HTPC, ITX and small models with a small CPU cooler without any memory limitation worries.

【Broad Compatibility】The heatsink supports CPU slots: Intel: LGA1700/1150/1151/1155/1156/1200; AMD/AM4/AM5, for different platforms, the heatsink is equipped with the corresponding metal mounting fasteners, which can be installed in conjunction with the manual or installation video.

【cpu cooler specifications】cpu cooling Size: 94.5×95×36mm, matched fan: TL-9015, air volume: 42.58CFM (MAX), air pressure: 1.33mmH2O (MAX), rotational speed: 2700RPM ± 10%, noise: 22.4db (A), fan pin: 4PIN PWM, radiator material: aluminum. The attached heat transfer paste can provide good cooling effect and improve the heat transfer of the CPU.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Dual Soldered Process Both Nickle plated copper base and four high performance heat pipes are soldered with fins for maximum heat transfer and withstand usage over long period of time. 100% RAM and PCIe compatibility Optimized heatsink design for compatibility for ITX motherboard, even the PCIe and RAM slots are close to CPU socket, AXP90-X low profile cooler is still compatible with high memory modules or thick PCIe cards. 36mm low profile height Fits in most small form factor case, even in OEM machines and smaller HTPCs, while TL-9015 slim fan is capable of generating airflow to cool heatsink and motherboard components.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great cooler for 65W and lower TDP
reviews.reviewText: Works like a charm, seriously low profile. Relatively easy to install...

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Work with ASRock DeskMini X300M mini PC and very quiet
reviews.reviewText: Replaced the original CPU cooler from ASRock DeskMini X300M and this low profile Thermalright version works well and very quiet so far.Easy to install with the tutorial video on the item page. Tips to install in narrow space, such as in ASRock X300M - adjust fan position gently to leave 2 - 3 mm gap to RAM or other motherboard components.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Marginally better than the stock intel cooler
reviews.reviewText: I have an i7 9700k (no OC) in a Dell XPS case which throttled during gaming under the stock cooler. Was hoping this would be enough cooling to avoid throttling but sadly it isn't. It cools roughly the same but does so with slightly lower fan noise. It may do better in a case with better air flow.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Work great for asrock desk mini 310

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This is the one low profile cooler I was looking for
reviews.reviewText: The other brand was not available for several days. After doing research, and instead of waiting, I decided to purchase this one. I couldn't be happier. Super quiet, inexpensive, ideal for my Deskmini/Ryzen 5 5600G.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars use as backup cooler
reviews.reviewText: My AIO is dead and buy this for backup / replacement until it returns from RMA.CPU is 13900kf, this cooler can handle the heat for non CPU intensive workload. ~50C at idle. For some games, could reach 100C. Just like what it advertises, near 95w TPD, more than that is going to hit the temperature wall. Anyway, this is not designed for high end CPU.The build quality of this product is good. Low profile, okay for itx complex case. I would still recommend Noctua's low profile cooler. However, this one is much cheaper, suitable for low budget build. I would recommend this for i3 CPU. For AMD 5000 series, ryzen 3. You don't need this if go for AMD 3000series, the cooler comes with the processor is much better than this.The pre-installed nuts and screws are too tight, takes me a while to release them with a plier. Installation is easy if you can have access to the back of the motherboard. Just install the cooler before mounting the motherboard to the case.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Don't tighten this too much, you will bend your motherboard. There are no "stops" that will prevent you from overtightening. On my Ryzen 5 4600G, at idle, it won't cool to below 88 C. At performance fan mode, It got to 80 C. The fit and finish of the heatsink is good, but it doesn't have the build quality to transfer heat effectively.
